President Biden has announced that Karine Jean-Pierre will be the next White House Press Secretary, replacing Jen Psaki who will leave on May 13. President Biden praised Jean-Pierre's experience, talent, and integrity, and expressed confidence in her ability to effectively communicate the work of the Biden-Harris Administration. Anita Dunn will also be returning as a Senior Advisor and Assistant to the President, bringing her wealth of experience as a communications and political strategist. Both Jean-Pierre and Dunn have extensive backgrounds in political roles and have previously worked with President Biden.